Feels great to finally start drawing again :D I figured since #inktober is starting soon I'd do a little warmup. .
So I'm new to the borderlands fandom and I wanted to redesign some of my favs, starting with zero. I find his dry sense of humor to be really funny and I really like those types of characters in general. This design is kinda like an upgraded suit, I tried to make it look like something he'd probably wear and I introduced the tan/cream color to give it more of a "veteran" type of vibe. .
For this year's inktober challenge I'm planning on making an original character based on the word for that day, I'm really looking forward to sharing the results!!!

caption.text:
NOTÍCIAS | Capcom disponibilizou hoje a fãs selecionados, códigos de resgate para download da beta de Project REsistance!

A beta começará dia 04 de Outubro e os jogadores selecionados poderão aproveitá-la até dia 07 de Outubro! Apesar de já baixar a aplicação, ao abrir o game não é possível joga-lo, apenas pode-se ver o teaser trailer seguido de uma breve introdução sobre a trama onde fala que os sobreviventes estão infectados por um vírus e estão sendo testados pela Umbrella para a corporação observar as reações da arma viral nos organismos das cobaias

Eu fui selecionado (graças a Deus, obrigado Capcom) e estarei jogando a beta esse final de semana, assim também trazendo conteúdos para vocês! Estou pensando em fazer uma live para falar melhor as minhas primeiras impressões. Caso você tenha se cadastrado para a beta, certifique-se de que não recebeu algum email da Capcom via programa Resident Evil Ambassador!

Hey, it's been awhile! Nice to see again! So your probably wondering "Where have you been and why is there a picture of Eggman doing some sort of model pose on my screen?" ... Well, I've been busy with stuff. That and the fact that I'm just really lazy. Anyways, I've been trying to get better with posting on this page. It is being worked on. As for the model pose, it was just a picture of me goofing around at Ani-bash 2019. I was looking back through old photos from past conventions and I found this gem. I decided to post it because it looked good to me. I've also noticed that some of the convention pictures have old friends that I used to go to conventions with standing next to me. It reminds me of the good old times before the falling out between us... Heh, it kinda stings actually... Anyways, I'll see you sometime soon. I'll try to post more often than usual even though I might have to force myself to do it. For now, please enjoy this picture of me trying to be pretty. I'll see you around.

""Hii my name is Ashley but I go by Ash. My gaming journey started when I was around 6 years old. I started on a Nintendo 64 playing Mario kart, Star Fox, and my all time favorite game Zelda: Ocarina of Time. I enjoy playing a variety of games from first-person shooters like CoD to games like Zelda, Minecraft, and even MOBAs. Even though I've been playing games for so long I am still an pretty average player, but that doesn't stop me from enjoying them. My favorite thing is playing together with my friends and getting to share our experiences. I wanted to bring my love of gaming out to the rest of the world and meet amazing people who enjoy the same things as me. Giants are a race of gargantuan humanoids found in the wilderness of Skyrim and High Rock. Infamous for their colossal height and immense strength, giants share little civil interaction with humans or elves, although they did have some alliances with the Dwemer.

Culturally, giants herd mammoths, processing their milk into cheese, complementing their omnivorous diet with the cooked meat of skeever. Seemingly nomadic, giants travel with their herds, setting camp across Skyrim and High Rock. Invaders are attacked with the massive clubs constructed by the giants.

Another day closer to our next panel, another day I get to share another photo of the all women panel. I could go on and on about amazing this cast was from an acting standpoint but instead I'll talk about it from a comradery standpoint. Comradery and chemistry are 2 very important things I look at when I'm putting together a cast, it helps tremendously when people know each other in an ensemble and even if they don't right away, it's a beautiful thing to watch it develop onstage as we go through the panel and see it really blossom when we get to the cold reading portion. Because Julie Nathanson was helping with casting, we really went for comradery when it came to selecting actors, you see this in a lot of ways from the banter between everyone during earlier parts of the panel to how our read went and elements like this really elevate a panel into standing out. By the end of the panel, we had friendships develop for everyone which is another important element for me and brings up a lesson I learned from Rob Paulsen which is "work with people you consider friends", before the panel, I maybe knew 5 out of 8 actors personally (Julie, Val, Elle, Rachel and Larissa) and now I consider them all good friends and it helped having Julie's magnetism when it came to bringing in amazing, wonderful people like Sara Cravens, Courtenay Taylor and Jen Hale and we really brought the best out of each other that day and again, I can't express enough gratitude to all these ladies for taking a chance and doing this panel with me as my first all women cast. 
Photo by @dl.visuals

caption.text:
Seven days of #kookievision, based on my latest Link's Awakening sugar cookie set. Day seven - the final day. Link. I saved our hero for last, of course. I kind of dig the new look that they gave him in the newly reimagined Link's Awakening. It's got this cute shiny toy appearance. I saw the new Amiibo figure of him (which I don't even collect), but I might have to snatch him up. Which was your favourite sugar cookie of the set?

If you want to see more, I created a 20 minute video compilation of the entire set. No instructions, no dialogue, just some music. Check out "Kookievision" on the Sweethart Baking Experiment YouTube channel to watch it.

For my favourite sugar cookie dough and royal icing recipe, visit the "How To" section of my website at sweethartbaking.com.

Do you love my cookie videos and want to see more? Check me out on Ko-Fi to make a small coffee-sized Paypal donation towards the future of Kookievision:
☕ ko-fi.com/sweethart

Music is "Powerup!" by Jeremy Blake from the YouTube audio library.

caption.text:
Quick Review - Final Fantasy 7 (1997)

After Final Fantasy 9 I had an itch that had to immediately be scratched by playing what most people consider the best game in the series. Well, I finally have and i'll tell you that I don't think it's perfect. Now dont take that as a diss, I loved this game and had a wonderful time playing it but it had a few quirks that drove me crazy. Most just relics of the time it was released. 
Of course by now the story was mostly spoiled for me but I will say that the BIG moment caught me off guard because I thought it happened at the end and not in the middle of the story.

Most of the gameplay was similar to FF9 so I got the hang of it quick and it was still enjoyable but it felt like the random encounters happened WAY more often in this game and it was kinda annoying. The other big thing that drove me crazy was navigating the world map. It would say things like go north and i'd get lost or turned around and none of the places were labeled so I had to keep a map pulled up on my phone to see where the hell I was supposed to go. Anytime I had to go to a new island i'd let out an audible sigh and trudge through it. 
I played the game on the Switch and I wont lie, I made use of the cheats. There are cheats to make the game run faster, turn off the random encounters and keep your meter maxed out. There were points where it started to feel like a chore to get through some areas and i'd just say screw it and use the cheats.

With all that being said, I had a lot of fun with the game. I can agree that it is a classic of the genre and it may be becuase of the more cyber/steampunk looking setting but I think I liked this one just SLIGHTLY more than 9. I even went and watched the Advent Children movie and I enjoyed that as well.

In the end, I had fun on my journey through the story and I even bought the FF8 remaster on Switch so my trek through the Final Fantasy series will continue.

9/10 - Brent
